{"lemma":"أَبْيَنانِ","slug":"أَبْيَنانِ","root":"ب.#.ن","root_slug":"ب-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3375","n3376","n3677"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3375","headword_ar":"اُبَيْنٌ","root":"bnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an unused, or unusual, dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3376","headword_ar":"اُبَيْنٍ","root":"bnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of the same measure as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uEayomK","text_ar":"اُعَيْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaY","text_ar":"اَبْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomaY","text_ar":"اَعْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, IB, Mgh,) and is quasi-pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) Mohammad is related, in a trad., to have said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayoniY laA taromuwA jamorapa","text_ar":"اُبَيْنِى لَا تَرْمُوا جَمْرَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEabaqabipi Hat~aY taToluEa Al$~amosu","text_ar":"العَبَقَبِةِ حَتَّى تَطْلُعَ الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O little"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dear"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sons, cast not ye the pebble of the 'Akabeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamorapN","text_ar":"جَمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until the sun rise"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayoniY~a Alx","text_ar":"اُبَيْنِىَّ الخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my little sons"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Mgh, TA:) IAth says that the hemzeh is augmentative; and that there are differences of opinion respecting the form of the word and its meaning: some say that it is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaY","text_ar":"اَبْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomaY","text_ar":"اَعْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", a sing. word denoting a pl. meaning, or, accord. to some, a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": some say that it is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [and if so, we must read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayoniY","text_ar":"اُبَيْنِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my little son;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] but this requires consideration [more especially as it is followed by a pl. verb]: AO says that it is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniY~a","text_ar":"بَنِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the affixed pronoun of the first pers. [sing.]; and this requires us to read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayoniY~a","text_ar":"اُبَيْنِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) J says, in the S, that the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayonaA='N","text_ar":"اُبَيْنَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and, if you will, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayonuwna","text_ar":"اُبَيْنُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he cites a verse in which occurs the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayoniyka","text_ar":"اُبَيْنِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the gen. case, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy little sons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and adds, it is as though its sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibonN","text_ar":"اـِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the disjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", whence the dim. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayonN","text_ar":"اُبَيْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubayonuwna","text_ar":"اُبَيْنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but he should have said, as though its sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaY","text_ar":"اَبْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomaY","text_ar":"اَعْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonawu","text_ar":"اَبْنَوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IB, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Sb","IB","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3677","headword_ar":"اَبْيَنُ","root":"byn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAy^inN","text_ar":"بَايِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^aboyanu mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَبْيَنُ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is more perspicuous, clear, distinct, chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent, in speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language, than such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86/","headword_ar":"أبين","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_21","lexicon_en":"Muḥammad al-Fattinī, Majmaʿ Biḥār al-Anwār fī Gharāʾib al-Tanzīl wa Laṭāʾif al-Akhbār (d. 1578 CE)","lexicon_ar":"مجمع بحار الأنوار للفَتِّنيّ","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=35110#44830e","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">[أبين]</span><span> وعدن أبين- بوزن أحمر: قرية على جانب البحر ناحية اليمن، وقيل: اسم مدينة عدن.</span>"}]}}